abstract = {Although four intergeneric cyprinid hybrid combinations (produced by cross- ing Semotilus atromaculatus with Campostoma anomalum, Clinostomus elongatus, Nocomis biguttatus, and Rhinichthys atratulus) all possessed intermediate hybrid indices, 21 of 34 characters were not intermediate. Only S. atromaculatus x N. biguttatus hybrids had a greater number of characters that were intermediate than were not. Divergence from intermediacy is not related to phylogenetic relation- ship among the crosses analyzed. The S. atromaculatus x C. anomalum experi- mental hybrids from Ohio populations differed in several respects from speci- mens analyzed by Cross and Minckley (1960) from Kansas and Nebraska. The number of lateral line scales and the ratio interorbital width/standard length were significantly different between two series of hybrids produced by crossing a male S. atromaculatus with two female C. anomalum from the same watershed. In both cases the index value of one series was intermediate but the value for the other series was not. These data support caution in assuming that phenotypic expression in hybrids is consistently intermediate, or that character expression is consistent among hybrids of the same cross. Certain trends in character expression existed among the four hybrid crosses analyzed. Knowledge of such trends may be useful in identification of unknown hybrid forms.},
